The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry (finding an upper bound on $-\log r(n,k)$), which suggests that it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The problem involves finding the minimum value of a certain expression, which involves integers, suggesting that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also mentions an algorithmic result, which further supports the possibility of it belonging to cs.DS or cs.CC. The use of logarithms and subexponential algorithms suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
